Frequently Asked Questions for ITT (NYSE:ITT)
What is ITT's stock symbol?

ITT trades on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) under the ticker symbol "ITT."



How often does ITT pay dividends? What is the dividend yield for ITT?

ITT announced a quarterly dividend on Wednesday, May 10th. Investors of record on Monday, June 12th will be paid a dividend of $0.128 per share on Monday, July 3rd. This represents a $0.51 annualized dividend and a yield of 1.23%. The ex-dividend date is Thursday, June 8th.  View ITT's Dividend History.



How were ITT's earnings last quarter?

ITT Inc. (NYSE:ITT) issued its quarterly earnings results on Monday, May, 8th. The company reported $0.64 earnings per share for the quarter, beating the Zacks' consensus estimate of $0.60 by $0.04. The firm earned $625.80 million during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $607.08 million. ITT had a net margin of 8.04% and a return on equity of 14.65%. The firm's revenue was up 2.7% on a year-over-year basis. During the same quarter in the prior year, the company earned $0.59 EPS.  View ITT's Earnings History.



What guidance has ITT issued on next quarter's earnings?

ITT issued an update on its FY17 earnings guidance on Monday, May, 8th. The company provided earnings per share (EPS) guidance of $2.205-2.505 for the period, compared to the Thomson Reuters consensus estimate of $2.38. The company issued revenue guidance of $2.357-2.453 billion, compared to the consensus revenue estimate of $2.45 billion.



Where is ITT's stock going? Where will ITT's stock price be in 2017?

8 brokers have issued 12 month price objectives for ITT's stock. Their predictions range from $40.00 to $51.00. On average, they anticipate ITT's share price to reach $46.67 in the next twelve months. View Analyst Ratings for ITT.



What are analysts saying about ITT stock?

Here are some recent quotes from research analysts about ITT stock: 
1. According to Zacks Investment Research, "ITT Inc. has a robust earnings surprise history, having beaten estimates thrice in the trailing four quarters. The company’s focus on business streamlining, cost controls and efficiency continues to prove beneficial to its financial performance. ITT Inc.’s diversified operations across key end markets adds to its strength. The company’s bottom line is expected to benefit from improved operating efficiency and successful cost containment actions. Further, ITT Inc.’s shares have outperformed the Zacks categorized Diversified Operations industry average over the past year. ITT Inc. has achieved operational excellence through its Lean Six Sigma program, restructuring initiatives and global sourcing efforts. However, softness in industrial, oil & gas markets and aerospace and defense business is expected to affect client spending adversely, thus restricting the company’s growth to a great extent." (7/18/2017)
2. UBS AG analysts commented, "ITT's Process business performed better than we had expected in 4Q but order declines accelerated to -17% (-3% sequentially), which stands in contrast to other oil & gas levered companies we cover, such as DOV and EMR, which have started showing signs of improvement. We think this has to do with ITT's lack of exposure to North American fracking, as most of the company's upstream business (~45% of total O&G) is in Latin America and the Middle East. Management remains cautious on its IP outlook, expecting oil & gas down LDD and chemical/industrial pumps down HSD; we think ITT shares are pricing in a faster recovery for the business, but there remains risk that the company could see a more protracted recovery than U.S. competitors, in our view." (2/16/2017)
3. Stifel Nicolaus analysts commented, "A reasonable and we think modestly conservative guide here with the main swing factor being primarily in ITT's short cycle pump business (which we think is more likely to be a bit better than a bit worse) with some potential upside from increasing rig count in ICS. Potential risks we see center primarily around rising input prices, mainly steel and copper. We believe IP and ICS will likely bottom in 2017 and while the voracity of any oil & gas recovery remains uncertain we expect significant growth in MT, benefits from carryover cost savings and price pressures to abate (well, at least be less of a headwind...) to drive ~20% EPS growth in 2018." (2/15/2017)




